article.headline: Liberty 64, Radford 48
article.story: RADFORD, Va. (AP) -- Alex McLean had 16 points and 11 rebounds to lead Liberty to a 64-48 win over Radford, snapping a 10-year losing streak at the Highlanders. The Flames (14-16, 8-6 Big South) never trailed after a jumper by Larry Blair, putting Liberty up 20-19 with 3:28 left in the half. Radford (8-21, 3-11) were outrebounded 44-29 and kept to 34 percent shooting, including 1-for-12 from 3-point range. The Flames, who led 31-25 at the half, went 44 percent from the field. Blair led Liberty with 17 points, and Anthony Smith added 11 points and eight rebounds. Chris Oliver led the Highlanders with 14 points and 11 rebounds, and Reggie McIntyre added 11 points.
